If there is already unindented content at a tag, when adding a tag:

* add indent in front of the text that is already there
* add a newline after the content that is already there

This is the current situation:

  <h1>
    <a href="/">
Arch      <font id="blue">Linux</font>
      <font id="gray">Norway</font>
    </a>
  </h1>

This is preferrable:

  <h1>
    <a href="/">
      Arch
      <font id="blue">Linux</font>
      <font id="gray">Norway</font>
    </a>
  </h1>

